<CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Angela Pancrazio -- Mercury News; SMOKEY THE CAT -- Burlingame
firefighters found this smoke-colored cat at 60 Elrod Ave. in Oakland.
Contributions for emergency services to animals can be made by check to the
Oakland SPCA Fire Fund, 8323 Baldwin St., Oakland 94621, or call (501)
569-0702.  </CAPTION>
<DESCRIPT>  EAST-BAY; FIRE; DISASTER; VOLUNTEER; CHARITY; AID; LIST  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  (box) Volunteers: In Santa Clara County, the Volunteer Exchange at (408)
286-1126 is keeping a list of those willing to volunteer to help fire
victims.; (box) Donations: Clothing, bedding, non-perishable food and bottled
drinks will be accepted at all Salvation Army thrift stores. All Bay Area
Safeway stores are accepting non-perishable food, diapers, batteries and
emergency supplies (no clothing). Lucky and Safeway stores also are accepting
donations of money.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Front  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  WHERE TO GIVE  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  The Oakland Hills Fire  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  (box) Clothing drive: Radio station KSOL in San Mateo will help gather
clothing donations from sites around the Bay Area and deliver it to relief
agencies. The station number is (415) 341-8777; fax number is (415) 574-9355.;
(box) Drop-off: The Campbell Seventh-day Adventist Church is accepting
donations of supplies and food. The drop-off center will be open from 9 a.m.
to 6:30 p.m. at 600 W. Campbell Ave., Campbell.; (box) Churches: The Council
of Churches of Santa Clara County has established an East Bay Fires Interfaith
Response Fund. All donations will be given to religious leaders in Oakland and
Berkeley to be distributed to victims. Donations can be sent to the Council of
Churches of Santa Clara County, 1229 Naglee Ave., San Jose 95126. Donors are
asked to note "fire" on checks.; (box) Relief Funds: Members of the Catholic
Diocese of San Jose are asked to contribute to the Disaster Relief Fund set up
by the Diocese of Oakland. Contributions can be sent to Diocese of Oakland
Disaster Relief Fund, 841 Lenzen Ave., San Jose 95126.; (box) Foundation: The
East Bay Community Foundation is accepting contributions to be given to
non-profit groups offering resettlement, counseling and other support
services. Send contributions to the East Bay Community Foundation, 6230
Claremont Ave., Fourth Floor, Oakland 94618, or call (510) 658-5441.; (box)
Fire fund: Donations also may be made to East Bay Emergency Fire Fund, United
Way at 410 Bush St., San Francisco 94108, or 1970 Broadway, No. 340, Oakland
94612. For more information, call (415) 772-HELP, (800) 273-6222, or TTY 554,
2445 for the hearing-impaired.; (box) Red Cross: Contributions can also be
sent to the American Red Cross at 2111 E. 14th St., Oakland 94606, or 1550
Sutter St., San Francisco 94109; or the Salvation Army at P.O. Box 2D, San
Jose 95109. The American Red Cross is accepting credit card donations at (510)
535-2812 or -2818.  </TEXT>
